The Adept creates a volume from which non-magical darkness is
partially or totally banished.  The volume is equal to 1000 cubic feet
(+ 500 cubic feet / Rank) and can be any shape the adept desires,
provided that no dimension is smaller than one foot.  The volume must
fall entirely within the range of the spell and, once cast, cannot be
moved.  At Ranks 0--5 the amount of darkness within the volume is
reduced to 10\% (appears as though lit on a cloudy day), at Ranks
6--10 it is reduced to 5\% (as though lit on a sunny day), at Ranks
11--15 it is reduced to 1\% (similar to daytime in a desert), and at
Ranks 16--20 all darkness is banished (i.e., totally light), so it is
impossible to see into or whilst within the volume (unless under the
effects of a Resistance to Light).  Note that because darkness is
being banished, no light is actually generated so any area outside the
volume will not be lit.  Hence this spell cannot create shadows even
though it is possible for an entity to be silhouetted against it.  If
it is not possible for an entity to see into a lit area then that
entity will not be able to see things within the lit area.  Any or all
of this volume can be overridden by a Spell of Darkness.
