{\em Effects:} Once this spell is cast, the target must remain still
in order for it to have effect.  While remaining still the target is
not able to be seen by non-magical means (i.e.  as for invisibility).
If the target moves, the spell ceases to work.  However, if the target
becomes still again during the duration of the spell, it will resume
its effect.  The duration of the spell refers to the time since
casting, not the time that the spell is actually in effect (i.e. while
the target is still).
